Obama put in place tougher rules on drone strikes in 2013 to cut down on civilian deaths, but CIA got an exemption . 
 President must sign off on drone strikes targeting suspects on 'kill list,' but operations against other suspected militants don't require his approval . 
 Obama took 'full responsibility' for January deaths of US hostage Dr Warren Weinstein and Italian aid worker Giovanni Lo Porto in drone strike . 
 Senator John McCain on Sunday said drone strikes against militants on foreign soil should be run by the US military and not the CIA . 
 